Treatment failure (relative risk [RR], 15.4; 95% confidence interval [CI], 10.6–22.4; 
     p < 0.001) and mortality (RR, 3.73; 95% CI, 2.13–6.53; 
     p < 0.001) were higher among new multidrug-resistant TB cases than among new susceptible cases.

Multidrug-resistant tuberculosis (adjusted odds ratio: 12.4 [95% confidence interval: 1.17–132.3]; 
     p = 0.037) was a risk factor for unfavorable outcome, and multidrug-resistant tuberculosis remained a risk for death (adjusted odds ratio: 63.9 [95% confidence interval: 4.84–843.2]; 
     p = 0.002).
